OL,6,FSmith said: "The way he had been
OL,7,Fthreatening staff members ` the threat
OL,8,Fwas the knife, to the staff there and
OL,9,Falso to himself."
OL,11,FThe court heard both Smith and Comotto
OL,12,Frepeatedly asked Mr Burgess to drop
OL,13,Fthe knife, with Smith warning him:
OL,14,F"Put the knife down mate, or you will
OL,15,Fbe sprayed or tasered. That's up to
OL,16,Fyou."
OL,18,FSmith told the court he believed Mr
OL,19,FBurgess "could clearly understand what
OL,20,Fwe were saying to him".
